Acidops fimbriatus
occurs in the eastern Pacific, from California, Mexico to Clipperton I. and the Galápagos ( Garth 1946 ; Hendrickx 1995 ;
Poupin et al. 2009
).
Acidops cessacii
has a wide distribution in the Atlantic, occurring from West Africa to Brazil (see Monod 1956 ; Manning & Holthuis 1981 ;
Barreto et al. 1993
; Melo 1996 ).
